				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Wow some people just don't seem to understand. If you don't have something useful, don't post.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Just a piece of advice...
<br />

<br />
Don't trash people that answered your call for help. 
<br />

<br />
Sure, Elliot deserved it for being such an a$$. You have all the rights to trash him back. Fortunatelly, people like Elliot that only feel realized when puting someone down is like 1% (if so) of EQDIVA population.
<br />

<br />
Cleador did post some helpfull advices, such as:
<br />

<br />
1- Use LUL (since you can't mez)
<br />
2- Get Fading Memories (you haven't stated your level anywhere so its not unreasonable to think a BoT player being 63. And even if you aren't 63, what he is saying is GET Fading Memories ASAP)
<br />

<br />
If as you say, you agro when using lul, then your charisma sucks, get more CHA thru AAs, or a shammy buff if possible. Will greatly improve your non-agro-lul-resists.
<br />

<br />
You can delay the agro on Group by using the no dmg SNARE. Just snare 1 giant on pull if other added, and bring non-snare giant to camp to shake agro, then get away from camp and keep mob snared and as far from group as possible. Mob will however agro group as soon as tank gets a CH though, but at least shammy can slow 2nd mob with 1st mob already slowed.
<br />

<br />
If you don't have mez, buy it, or farm Ethereal Parchments from Hogobblins in PoN. While it doesn't mez Milities Giants (level 63) or Krigers (level 64) it will mez all other giants. Tell the group you cannot mez Milities and to attack Milities if they add and other giant is mezzable by level 62 spell. You can mez or kite Elementals, since they don't summon and are level 62 (Chants will keep agro on you, about the only spell that will).
<br />

<br />
Have a ranger snare kite the add, or for someone to root/park it. 
<br />

<br />
Get Fading Memories ASAP.
<br />

<br />
As for getting agro on adds so you can kite them while group kills target, you can pretty much forget about it... it will never happen.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
